en.blogDescription: The International Student Society (ISS) Egypt has truly made remarkable strides in fostering a vibrant and inclusive community, leaving an indelible mark on the academic and social landscape. Through a rich tapestry of events and initiatives, ISS Egypt has demonstrated unwavering dedication to its members and the broader community. From meticulously organized academic symposiums that ignite intellectual curiosity to culturally enriching gatherings that celebrate diversity, ISS Egypt has showcased an impressive range of accomplishments. Their commitment to newcomers is especially noteworthy, as they extend a warm embrace to new students, easing their transition into the academic world. Moreover, during the sacred month of Ramadan, ISS Egypt's events have created a sense of togetherness and spirituality, embodying the essence of unity. Additionally, their Islamic events have served as platforms for deepening faith and understanding. In sum, ISS Egypt's achievements in organizing social, academic, cultural events, as well as their dedicated support for newcomers and the observance of important traditions, exemplify their outstanding commitment to fostering a vibrant and harmonious community.
en.ISSEventDescription1: It offered a glimpse into how ISS Egypt celebrates Eid in partnership with other student societies such as ISS Yemen, Sudan, and many more at UTM. There were other activities, such as free face painting for children and free henna for girls.
en.ISSEventDescription2: All Arabic societies at UTM University were pleased to organize an event for a special Arabic breakfast. It was a big event where students enjoyed the best Arabic food and the magical Ramadan atmosphere.
en.ISSEventDescription3: On May 3rd, the majority of the Arabic Student Societies and the UTM MPP came together to express sympathy and support for Palestine.
en.AcademicEventDescription1: We conducted a webinar to learn more about the Skilled Migration requirements for Engineers, IT Professionals, and other occupations that are currently in demand in Australia!
en.AcademicEventDescription2: Revised Math 1 for the ISS students. The revision was held on 15th and 16th of December 2023
en.AcademicEventDescription3: Revised Chemistry Curriculum for Foundation and Bridging Students. It offered our students a unique opportunity to delve into the core principles of chemistry and enhance their academic prowess
en.AcademicEventDescription4: Eng Mohamed Aly revised Digital Electronics for Finals for Electrical students. We provided a comprehensive revision platform, nurtured collaborative learning, and deepened fundamental concepts' understanding.
en.AcademicEventDescription5: Eng Amro carried out a system modelling revision for the finals to aid students with their problems regarding this topic. He also solved a past test to give them a hint about how their exam will be.
en.AcademicEventDescription6: This seminar taught students excellent ideas and tactics for achieving in academic, professional, and extracurricular competitions, ranging from explaining how to find competitions to strategies for simply winning them.
en.AcademicEventDescription7: A four-day Web Applications Security 101 session was conducted with the CyberX team, covering website development, Linux operating system fundamentals, and website protection and hacking. Competitors will receive rewards on the final day.
en.AcademicEventDescription8: A quick session was held to assist students in learningÂ more about Germany and how to study there and acquire a visa; it also addressed challenges such as living expenses, studies, higher education, master's degrees, life in general, and more.
en.SocialEventDescription1: It was an event where all Egyptian students and prominent guests could attend the Welcome Day reception and breakfast together and get to know each other, particularly new students. Students who succeeded academically and were distinguished by their accomplishments or membership in clubs were honored.
en.SocialEventDescription2: In compliance with our duty towards the Palestinian issue, we, the Association of Arab Communities at UTM University, held a symposium for Palestine.
en.SocialEventDescription3: A school trip was organized to introduce students to university, foster connections with future generations, and encourage them to choose the appropriate major for their university career.
en.SocialEventDescription4: Students took a trip to Melaka to keep their minds off of their studies. The trip lasted for one day, and theyÂ visited several sights, including Masjid Selat Melaka, Dutch Square, andÂ A'Famosa, and even went on a river cruise.
en.CultureEventDescription1: Both ISS Egypt and Yemen cooperated to conduct one of the largest Islamic tournaments in UTM. It was separated into three sections: Hifz (Al Kahf, 1, 3, and 5 Chapters), Telawah, and Hadith.
en.CultureEventTitle2: Ramadan; Fasting of the Eyes and Tongue
en.CultureEventDescription2: It was an event to greet Ramadan by explaining to students that fasting isn't just about stopping eating; there are other things we need to stop doing, such as fasting with the eye and tongue.
en.CultureEventDescription3: Because the Semitic Arabic language is an essential language for us; speaking, considering, and comprehending, the Cultural Committee hosted an Arabic Language event highlighting the magnificence of the Arabic Language.
en.ReadingEventDescription1: Reading Club conducted a meeting to address the importance of reading and its role in building personality, sound reading skills, and Dr. Hatem bin Humaid journey with reading.
en.ReadingEventDescription2: The Reading Club and Cultural Committee organized a seminar to promote the importance of the Arabic language, its impact on languages, daily use, language sources, books, and benefits.
en.SportsEventDescription1: A Futsal League was organized amongst teams from various countries to determine whichÂ would hold the league cup.
en.WomenEventDescription1: The "Iftar Ramadan Gathering," an iftar hosted by the girls' representatives, was a lovely evening of celebration, unity, and spirituality that was exclusively for females. Together, attendees enjoyed in a delicious iftar, which was complemented by a nostalgic movie screening.  Furthermore, "Iftar Ramadan Gathering" offered a unique experience throughout the holy monthÂ ofÂ Ramadan.
